main event: Two missile-like objects were observed over Monrovia, Liberia on November 9, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be 3/4 the size of the moon., The sighting occurred at an elevation of 15-20 degrees above the horizon., Many reports indicated bright lights with luminous spiral trails., The objects were observed at approximately 10,000 feet., Conditions at the time were clear and cloudless with a bright three-quarter moon.
witness description: many reports received detailing the sightings
